From: AgenticBrowser <build@agentic-browser.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] Add binary-level timezone override flag

Detection vector: Some detection sites read timezone from both
JavaScript (Intl.DateTimeFormat) and the TLS/HTTP layer. If they
disagree, the mismatch reveals proxy/VPN usage. JS-level timezone
overrides via CDP can be detected by checking the property descriptor.

This patch adds a --ab-timezone=<IANA> flag that sets the timezone
at the ICU/binary level, ensuring all timezone sources agree.

Surface: intl
Closes: timezone inconsistency between JS and network layers

--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/wtf/date_math.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/wtf/date_math.cc
@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@ void InitializeTimezone() {
+  // AgenticBrowser: if --ab-timezone=<IANA> is set, use it instead
+  // of the system timezone. This ensures Intl.DateTimeFormat, Date,
+  // and all timezone-dependent APIs report the same value.
+  if (!ab_timezone_.empty()) {
+    setenv("TZ", ab_timezone_.c_str(), 1);
+    tzset();
+  }
